HEADWORD: Alnage
<hw>Al"nage</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l"n⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>, <ety>[OF.
<ets>alnage</ets>, <ets>aulnage</ets>, F. <ets>aunage</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>alne</ets> ell, of Ger. origin: cf. OHG. <ets>elina</ets>, Goth.
<ets>aleina</ets>, cubit. See <er>Ell</er>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>Measurement (of cloth) by the ell; also, a duty for such
measurement.</def>⟦br⟧
